race.comment: NADAL (3) won the inaugural edition of this race last year with a blistering performance, coming from a mile back to win by nearly three lengths. He was off an injury leading into this campaign. First up he did enough over an unsuitable 1000m when peaking late before travelling well at Flemington when well supported but clearly hating the very heavy ground, dropping right out when the pressure came. Suspect he can bounce back. JIGSAW (2) is flying. He backed up the win here with another speedy performance in the G2 McEwen Stakes at Moonee Valley. He'll give a huge sight out in front. ARKANSAW KID (1) is off a short spell but has the class to take this out, can't discount. NEED SOME LUCK (6) relished the heavy ground to win well at Flemington. Goes in all conditions and should run very well again. HEDGED (8) is going well without luck his past couple. There was nothing between him and JIGSAW here prior, he can break through.
